title: Pullback of Riemannian metrics
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

If $$f\colon M^m\to N^n$$ is a smooth map, we can pull back sections of $$\mathrm Q(\T N)$$ to sections of $$\mathrm Q(\T M)$$ in the natural way:
$$
(f^* g)(X_p,Y_p)\coloneqq g(f_* X_p, f_* Y_p).
$$
$$f^* g$$ is a [[Riemannian metric]] if and only if $$f$$ is an [[immersion|Immersion und Submersion]].